Uasin Gishu County Commissioner Abdi Hassan has raised concerns about the high number of cases of defilement of children and early pregnancies. He said the majority of cases are resolved through illegal kangaroo courts and negotiations, leaving the victims to suffer while suspects evade justice.He says the communities must ensure that those who perpetrate defilement face the law.Abdi spoke at a meeting for the Mandeleo Ya Wanawake Organization (MYWO) who have now pledged to help to fight increasing cases of defilement of children and domestic violence in the region.